#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:4
msgid "Inter-VM Shared Memory device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:6
msgid ""
"On Linux hosts, a shared memory device is available. The basic syntax is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:11
msgid "|qemu_system_x86| -device ivshmem-plain,memdev=hostmem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:13
msgid ""
"where hostmem names a host memory backend. For a POSIX shared memory "
"backend, use something like"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:18
msgid ""
"-object memory-backend-file,size=1M,share,mem-path=/dev/shm/ivshmem,"
"id=hostmem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:20
msgid ""
"If desired, interrupts can be sent between guest VMs accessing the same "
"shared memory region. Interrupt support requires using a shared memory "
"server and using a chardev socket to connect to it. The code for the shared "
"memory server is qemu.git/contrib/ivshmem-server. An example syntax when "
"using the shared memory server is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:28
msgid ""
"# First start the ivshmem server once and for all\n"
"ivshmem-server -p pidfile -S path -m shm-name -l shm-size -n vectors\n"
"\n"
"# Then start your qemu instances with matching arguments\n"
"|qemu_system_x86| -device ivshmem-doorbell,vectors=vectors,chardev=id\n"
"                 -chardev socket,path=path,id=id"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:35
msgid ""
"When using the server, the guest will be assigned a VM ID (>=0) that allows "
"guests using the same server to communicate via interrupts. Guests can read "
"their VM ID from a device register (see ivshmem-spec.txt)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:41
msgid "Migration with ivshmem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:43
msgid ""
"With device property ``master=on``, the guest will copy the shared memory on "
"migration to the destination host. With ``master=off``, the guest will not "
"be able to migrate with the device attached. In the latter case, the device "
"should be detached and then reattached after migration using the PCI hotplug "
"support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:49
msgid ""
"At most one of the devices sharing the same memory can be master. The master "
"must complete migration before you plug back the other devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:53
msgid "ivshmem and hugepages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:55
msgid ""
"Instead of specifying the <shm size> using POSIX shm, you may specify a "
"memory backend that has hugepage support:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:60
msgid ""
"|qemu_system_x86| -object memory-backend-file,size=1G,mem-path=/dev/"
"hugepages/my-shmem-file,share,id=mb1\n"
"                 -device ivshmem-plain,memdev=mb1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/devices/ivshmem.rst:63
msgid ""
"ivshmem-server also supports hugepages mount points with the ``-m`` memory "
"path argument."
msgstr ""
